ğŸ¡
It was like a little village in the city, close to the sea, yet still only 5 minutes away from the city center. As soon as we walked into our future street and we saw these old little houses, we knew we wanted to live here.
ğŸ‘«
It was our first home together in Copenhagen, the place where we made our first memories, the first place we absolutely loved as well - apart from a few things we should not forget like the silverfish in the bathroom, the scary, humid-smelling basement that I avoided at all costs, and the agreement that we had to leave the apartment every time potential buyers would visit the place.
ğŸ’­
Although I love our new, gorgeous apartment which is 100% ours for 2 years, I am surprised as to how hard it is for me to say goodbye to a home. I have done this before, and either I have forgotten how difficult it is, or one simply never gets used to it. I guess that slowly but surely the sadness that is sticking to the good memories will start to crumble and only beautiful memories will remain.
ğŸ’—

Bryggervangen and Skt. Kjelds Plads that are a part of the Climate Neighborhood will be inaugurated Saturday, February 23rd. THIRD NATURE is the creator behind the 100 ha big master plan, that since 2012 has created the framework for the development of the Climate Neighbourhood. We are proud to see the project carried out in reality and would like to congratulate Copenhagen and Ã˜sterbro on its renewed neighbourhood, as well as SLA and all involved players who over the years have contributed to the realisation of the vision. We hope that this approach can lead the way and show how cities can handle climate change, while creating good places to live.

Everything about this shoot was neatly planned, except for a location. I wanted some old, abandoned building, but just couldn't find one.
As we got closer and closer to the shooting date, I got more and more desperate. I ended up finding this old house, that had earlier on been abandoned, but was some sort of gathering place for young, experimental and cultural projects. I got permission to shoot there 22 hours before the shoot started! That was a little tooooo exiting ğŸ˜‚
.
But the place was amazing! So many different rooms and exciting looks. We had a lot of fun working out what look to pur where. And in the end, I think it all came together in the most amazing way! ğŸ’–ğŸ’€ğŸ–¤ This shoot was published in @tenebrousmagazine

Smagen er helt utrolig ğŸ˜I was really struck by the power and beauty of these words of The Buddha from the Sutta Nipata. 
Too often we waste our time with idle chatter and gossip. We make a lot of noise that actually means very little. We trumpet our opinions for all to hear and attach great importance to having them accepted and validated. 
We say words that harm and belittle others. All in an attempt to make ourselves feel bigger. 
The real power lies in taking time to silence the constant stream of empty words and connect with the deep flow of consciousness from which we all originate. 
When you make this effort your words canâ€™t help but be fewer, yet they will be words of meaning, truth, kindness and compassion. Words that build and encourage. Words that matter! 
Be the mighty river not the tiny stream!
Happy Humpday yâ€™all!!ğŸ•‰

Believe me when I say that this is a MUST, you do NOT wanna miss eating a decadent semla, or a thousand, haha.
For those of you not familiar with it, a semla is an almost surreal -such a biased appreciation, I know- cardamom-y bun filled with sugary almond paste, whipped cream and topped off with powdered sugar. It is one of Swedenâ€™s best things, period.
At Juno, they add chopped toasted almonds, which provides an interesting textural contrast.

I have set up a membership with @theorganicclub_oesterbro and @detkollektiveklaedeskab 
Which is a collective wardrobe where you pay a monthly membership and can hand in good quality second hand clothes and swap for others clothes. 
I love that idea because it helps reduce the amount of clothes I have at home and I can still update my wardrobe without buying new clothes. It Takes 2,700 Liters Of Water To Make One T-Shirt so I think buying second hand is a great way to help reduce waste and water usage. 
I believe small steps can make a real difference and having less throw a way fashion is something I think is really important. 
Having spent 10 years in retail I have seen first hand how the corporate world makes us believe we need a lot of things to be happy which isnâ€™t true.

Enfants Terribles alias Nana et Matvey er en kunstnerduo, der bestÃ¥r af Nana RosenÃ¸rn Holland Bastrup (f. 1987 i KÃ¸benhavn) og Matvey Slavin (f. 1987 i Leningrad, (Sankt Petersborg), Rusland). Duoen Enfants Terribles blev grundlagt i Hamborg i 2012 og opkaldt efter deres installation af samme navn, som i maj 2012 blev vist pÃ¥ pladsen foran Hamburger Kunsthalle i Hamborg. Installationen var en hyldest til edderkoppeskulpturen Maman af Louise Bourgeois og bestod af seksten baby-edderkopper placeret rundt om BourgeoisÂ´ skulptur.
I 2014 opfandt duoen en betegnelse, som de kalder Laufbilder. Udgangspunktet for Laufbilderne er fotomateriale fra tidligere udstillinger, happeninger eller steder de har boet, som med inkjet bliver trykt pÃ¥ genbrugspapir. Kunstnerduoens motto er â€kunst er fodarbejdeâ€. Laufbilder (lÃ¸bende billeder) genskaber udstillingssituationer, som Enfants Terribles har realiseret i fortiden. VÃ¦rkerne behandler samfundsrelevante problemstillinger og reflekterer kritisk kunstmarkedet, kunstscenen, og den rolle, kunstnerne har i disse. Bastrup og Slavin forbinder deres kunstkarriere med symbolske elementer, forbindelser og groteske situationer. De agerende figurer, der forekommer i kunstnerduoens vÃ¦rker, hentes med inspiration fra deres personlige engagement i kunstscenen.

Visuals: @jonatanbrusch
Soundscapes: @allanhjorth & Signe R. Larsen

Project description: 
Still Motus is an eternally looping animation video with shifting soundscapes, about the never changing but constantly looping transformation of the world. The video itself represents a visualization of a world in constant motion but never changing. Only the soundscape changes occasionally, changing the mood but never the events that take place.

Nana Bastrups nye vÃ¦rker kredser om leg med identitet. SÃ¦rligt forklÃ¦dningen i form af masken er i fokus - enten som vÃ¦rende farvestrÃ¥lende/farvefattig,  tiltrÃ¦kkende/frastÃ¸dende eller lÃ¸ssluppen/hÃ¦mmende. 
Bastrups vÃ¦rker fremstÃ¥r fragmentariske og sammensatte og suger beskueren ind i et univers mellem fotodokumentation og fantasi. #baby #babypude #babymadras #babyshower #sari #vintage #vintagesari #sarimadras#indretning #interior #interiordesign #decor #decoration #dekoration #bohemian #boligindretning #boligmagasinet #cozyliving #cozy #inspiration #indretningsinspiration #smukkefarver #cultureliving #nordrefrihavnsgade27 #Ã¸sterbro #kÃ¸benhavnI dagene op til Ã¥bningen af gruppeudstillingen REMIX # 5 d. 24. januar prÃ¦senterer vi alle de 28 deltagende kunstnere.

Kunstner nr. 24: @igor.bleischwitz (f. 1981) bor og arbejder i Berlin.
Foto: fragment af vÃ¦rket "Toy" 42x30 cm, olie pÃ¥ lÃ¦rred, 2018, der udstilles i Kunstmix. "
I usually start to paint in a realistic manner. During the entire process I abstract, paint over the realistic painting. At the end we just see "remnants" from the motif before. 
They have something from the fragmental, the lost. At the same time, these â€œremnantsâ€ are part of something bigger and as fragments become all the more important because they are practically the only carriers of the original information. It is a kind of abstraction and selection with which I can show the essence without getting lost in the surface decorations 
My technique is quite wide-ranging - I experiment a lot to arrive at new solutions. In addition to brush and paint, in the last few years Iâ€™ve used a palette knife as my main painting tool.
The paintings painted in this technique visually differ a lot from my earlier works, which were consequently painted with a brush. There are also experiments with different painting materials, oils and pigments. I grind pigments myself and have therefore full control over the outcome.
Like any technique, it offers new opportunities and also has its limitations. My goal is to take the best from it and to constantly expand my knowledge. To me it is especially important that my work continues to evolve and that its strength and quality increase. With quality I mean, for example, that the paintings express sensitivity and vitality, a kind of feedback from the lived or the experienced. 
The works are included in series. They show different ways of approach in the process of painting. "

Serien â€Leaving it All Behindâ€ er mit forsÃ¸g pÃ¥ at isolere centrale dele i det at gÃ¸re et maleriet ved at isolerer maleriet i dele. I billedet her er motivet lÃ¸srevet fra fladen. Maleriet virker ufuldendt og det kan jeg godt lide. Min hÃ¥nd har ikke malet fuglen og alligevel har jeg ejerskabet til hver en tomme. 
For mig bÃ¦re maleriet pÃ¥ en hemmelighed. Derfor vil jeg gerne vise det. 
Simon Grimm er uddannet fra det Det Kgl. Danske Kunstakademi 1996-2003.

Maleriet â€VÃ¦gtenâ€ indgÃ¥r i min nyeste serie malerier kaldet [ Fone ]. I denne serie arbejder jeg med det transformative og undersÃ¸ger overfÃ¸rslen af udtryk og oplevelse fra et medie til et andet.
